I'm ADHD and suffer from anxiety and depression. These call all resemble bipolar but I am not bipolar. I lack mania. Hyperactivity can look like mania. Distractibility and inattentiveness can be misinterpreted as well. Perhaps BP2 or what used to be called Major Depressive Disorder. Point is, with so many overlapping symptoms diagnoses between this disorders as well as others are often wrong. Professional examination and testing beyond a GP is required and even then sometimes they get it wrong. Just a note from my 20+ years of struggle to find a proper diagnosis.
